# Per-rung scratch dirs (`rootless`: staged store + DB snapshot; `oci-load`:
# OCI layouts + corrupted-archive control; `td-builder`: staged store +
# registration record; `generation-image`: validator image extraction; `run`:
# archive + unpacked rootfs); kept on a red run for triage, removed on green.
.rootless-scratch/
.oci-load-scratch/
.td-builder-scratch/
.genimg-scratch/
.run-scratch/
.memo-scratch/
.registry-check-scratch/
.verify-place-check-scratch/
.store-register-scratch/
.store-add-scratch/
.store-add-tree-scratch/
.store-gc-scratch/
.store-gc-sweep-scratch/
.store-verify-scratch/
.store-add-referenced-scratch/
.build-hermetic-scratch/
.build-daemon-scratch/
# cargo-test: scratch CARGO_HOME + CARGO_TARGET_DIR (clean compile each run).
.cargo-test-scratch/

# check-memo verdicts (plan/check-memo.md constraint 2): host-local state,
# NEVER committed — a verdict greens only the environment that recorded it.
.check-verdicts/

# td-check-repro verdicts (plan/fast-check.md): same host-local, never-committed
# rule — memoizes the td-builder check double-build (kept separate from
# .check-verdicts/ to avoid the per-drv verdict-filename collision).
.td-check-verdicts/

# CI store image staging (ci/build-ci-image.sh default workdir; ~65G).
.ci-image-work/
.store-backend-scratch/

# Persistent content-addressed build-recipe cache (skip-if-already-realized).
.td-build-cache/

# Daily-backstop runner state (ci/daily-full-suite.sh): last all-green main commit +
# the latest machine-readable verdict. Local to the runner host, not versioned.
.td-last-green
.td-daily-verdict
